  "mitigation_currently_implemented": "Implement a more stringent egress ICMP rate limit on the UbuntuComputer OUTPUT chain, reducing the allowed ICMP echo-request rate well below the attack rate (e.g., 1-2 packets per second) to effectively throttle or disrupt the ongoing flood",
  "comments": "I applied a stricter ICMP echo-request rate limit on the OUTPUT chain of the compromised UbuntuComputer host, lowering the accepted rate to 2 packets per second with a burst of 2, and dropping all additional ICMP echo-requests. This further throttles the attack at the source, making it much more difficult for the ICMP flood to succeed while maintaining some level of legitimate ICMP traffic for normal network functionality. This respects the constraint of keeping the compromised host and attacker active while mitigating the attack.",
  "device_identifier": "UbuntuComputer",
  "commands": [
    "iptables -I OUTPUT -p icmp --icmp-type echo-request -m limit --limit 2/sec --limit-burst 2 -j ACCEPT",
    "iptables -A OUTPUT -p icmp --icmp-type echo-request -j DROP"
  ]
}
